Networking Models and Protocols
Today I learned about how devices talk to each other on a network.

The OSI Model has seven parts:

* Physical
* Data Link
* Network
* Transport
* Session
* Presentation
* Application

Each part does a job when sending data from one device to another.
The trainer showed us how it all works.
I also studied the TCP/IP Model, which is used a lot on the Internet.
Comparing the OSI Model and TCP/IP Model helped me understand real-world networking.

The trainer introduced protocols like:
1. HTTP
2. HTTPS
3. FTP
4. SSH
5. DNS
6. DHCP
7. TCP
8. UDP
9. ICMP

These protocols help devices exchange data safely and reliably
Understanding these protocols made me feel more confident, about networking.
The session was really helpful.
